result.execSummary:
The defendant John T Lewis Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Threat of Force, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Total term of imprisonment of 4 years; 2 years initial term of confinement; 2 years extended supervision, consecutive with credit for 51 days time served. Sentence STAYED and defendant placed on probation.
Conditions of extended supervision same as probation with the exception of condition house/DRC time.

miscConds.notes:
Terms of probation and extended supervision:
-9 months condition time in the House of Correction-good time to apply; Huber for work and treatment-conditional upon absolute sobriety.  Authorized to serve at DRC if accepted.
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with the Department
-Possess no weapons
-AODA assessment and cooperate with any treatment
-Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens
-No contact with Mayfair
-Obtain Mental health assessment and take all prescribed medications.
-Seek and maintain full time employment
-Obtain HSED or GED
Defendant to pay restitution $300 to Macy's from bail on deposit.
The court ordered defendant provide DNA sample--pay surcharge from bail on deposit.
The Court ordered all applicable costs, fees and surcharges to be paid from bail on deposit.  Any balance owing to be paid over probation; balance converted to civil judgment.  Upon revocation, through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant. Upon revocation defendant IS ELIGIBLE for CIP & WSAP.

timeConds.notes: Huber for work, treatment-conditional upon absolute sobriety.  Authorized to serve at DRC if accepted. Good time to apply.
